1
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:13,200
Are you Shark Yongke?

2
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,400
If he’s an idol, he should be able to sing, right?

3
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,040
Go on, please sing.
The passengers are waiting to hear you.

4
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:22,920
Wait, wait, do you need to take a dump?

5
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:24,480
All-New. Kreetha!

6
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:27,760
Kreetha and I will get you and Siri out of here.

7
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,920
You can count on us.

8
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:31,120
We have to find out who Mr. Glam is.

9
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,280
How could you not know?

10
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,520
You’re the one closest to Mr. Glam.

11
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,160
Or...

12
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:35,800
What is it?

13
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:36,800
You’re Mr. Glam?

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,760
How are you doing?

15
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,760
Hello, Chai.

16
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,720
We'll have a long meeting today.

17
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,160
Is everything okay?

18
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,160
Everything is going well, Chai.

19
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:05,960
It's time.

20
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:14,120
Even though I'm in a child's body but I got a brain of an adult.

21
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:16,120
This is nothing ordinary...

22
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:19,200
No matter who you are...

23
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,200
There is always only one truth!

24
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:27,040
Isn't that too much of a scene, Mr. Mouri Kogoro?

25
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,120
I'm Detective Conan!

26
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:30,920
Conan...

27
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,440
But it's time to go big, really.

28
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:36,600
Because we don't know what's gonna happen after this.

29
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:41,080
But what's important is we must find out who Mr. Glam really is.

30
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:44,760
And who is he?

31
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,440
I don't know, that's why I asked.

32
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:50,040
How could you not know, Chai?

33
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,520
You’re the one closest to Mr. Glam.

34
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,600
Closest one?

35
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,680
I only talk to him on the phone.

36
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,560
But what I'm certain is that...

37
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,920
he is abroad.

38
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:04,280
Man, that, everyone knows, Chai.

39
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:08,280
You're close to Mr. Glam? No! But I am...

40
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,400
Hey, Sky!

41
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:13,080
Don't tell me you got Mr. Glam's info?

42
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,560
It's top secret.

43
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:19,360
Wait, why don't you guys possess me if you're gonna be this close?

44
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:25,160
What I know about Mr. Glam is that...

45
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,600
he's in a good shape.

46
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,000
His face is oval.

47
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,920
His figure is astonishing.

48
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:32,520
His skin is bright like light bulbs.

49
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,200
He's got a prominent nose.

50
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,200
He's got Mazda lips.

51
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,080
He's got cockle eyes.

52
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:40,760
That's it, Sky.
That's what's gonna take us to Mr. Glam.

53
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,760
Ugh, guys, you're too easy to fool.

54
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:47,760
That's Mr. Glam's information that Sky made up to fool Madam Porn.

55
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,360
So what does this Mr. Glam look like?

56
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,800
Oh my, if you’re talking about our boss, Mr. Glam...

57
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:57,560
he’s one of a kind, you could find a man like him once in a hundred years.

58
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:00,600
Tall, lean, long legs. Narrow eyes behind glasses.

59
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,600
Mazda lips, cockle eyes.

60
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:06,360
Chaba, you're so good at memorizing stuff...

61
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,680
Well, who would believe such a story?

62
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:10,080
Madam Porn did.

63
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,640
Well, only Madam Porn did.

64
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,640
I did too.

65
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,560
Hey!

66
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,840
Chaba, it's time to fly.

67
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:21,960
Alright then, Chai and Tid-Gift, you two keep working on it, okay?

68
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:23,720
We'll get going now.

69
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,600
Okay?

70
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,120
Let's go.

71
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:29,760
Hey, Chaba, Sky, wait!

72
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:30,760
Wait!

73
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,160
So what do we do now?

74
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:41,280
If we can't find Mr. Glam...

75
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,960
but he finds us first...

76
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,680
he might kill us one by one.

77
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,160
We'll be doomed for sure.

78
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,920
If you don't help, Tid-Gift, you'll be doomed for sure.

79
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,560
Think, think!

80
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:54,560
I'm thinking!

81
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,520
I got it!

82
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:00,040
So what is it?

83
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:02,040
Or...Chai...

84
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,640
You're Mr. Glam?

85
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:24,680
Hey, Porn, what's wrong?
You look stressed, bro.

86
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:28,320
Siri, what did you call me earlier?

87
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,400
Porn...

88
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,480
What did you just call me?

89
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,880
Porn...

90
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:36,880
What? Siri! You’ve only been here a little while,
are you trying to blend in?

91
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,480
So what, Porn?

92
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:41,000
I’ll give you one more chance to call me properly.

93
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,160
Madam Porn.

94
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:47,040
Hey, Porn, listen, my friend.

95
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:51,040
Behind these walls, we’re all equal. Look!

96
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,440
"Everyone is equal."

97
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,920
Even if you used to be my boss before,

98
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:01,920
here, we’re friends, okay, Porn?

99
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,520
Okay, Siri.

100
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:11,520
But remember this, I’m the one who pays.

101
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:15,880
If I get out, you get out too.

102
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:19,080
That’s what you call being an adult.

103
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:25,080
No matter where I am or what I am,
I always hold you up highest, Madam.

104
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,000
Don’t flatter me.

105
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:33,120
I know, right now, I’m at the lowest point of my life.

106
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,520
Oh no, not true, Madam. We’ll get out soon.

107
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:40,520
Oh, come on, we're charged with serious offenses
and you still think we’ll get out?

108
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:44,760
The only way to get out of here is to break out of prison.

109
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,080
Break out of prison...

110
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:51,160
Oh my God! I can’t believe it!

111
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:56,200
Finally, that most stupid idea you told me you’d do...

112
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,120
today, it actually worked.

113
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,120
Come on, let me see it.

114
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,280
He's a cutie.

115
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:24,680
What? Are you into hot nerds now?

116
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:29,960
No, this is Shark Yongke.
He's dancing to Medium Rare on Toktok.

117
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:31,960
He's super cute. Take a look!

118
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:39,120
Chaba!

119
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,960
Huh?

120
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,720
There are lots of passengers today.

121
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,560
Why are you still watching videos of a guy?

122
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,120
Well, that's true.

123
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,400
This is a flight to Korea.

124
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,760
The passengers are so packed
they almost have to sit on the plane wings now.

125
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:49,760
There are too many!

126
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:56,600
Sky, do you think that gentleman looks familiar?

127
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:02,200
Yeah, I can't think of where I've seen him...

128
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,800
Is he Shark?

129
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,040
Which Shark? Baby Shark?

130
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:09,400
No! Shark Yongke, of course.

131
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,400
The one who dances to Medium Rare.
He's an idol.

132
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,240
Let me, let me!

133
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,760
Are you Shark Yongke?

134
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,320
I'm not gonna tell anyone.

135
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,720
Isn't it very hot, sir?

136
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,360
You're wearing a hoodie.

137
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,920
Are you wearing a heattech too?

138
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,720
It must be very hot for you.

139
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,720
I don't believe you.

140
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,720
You must be Shark Yongke for sure.

141
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,360
Sir!

142
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:48,760
You forgot your bag.

143
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:51,680
Thank you.

144
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:52,680
You're welcome.

145
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,360
Do you think he's Shark Yongke?

146
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,000
Are you nuts? What Yongke?

147
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,840
If you wanna see an idol...

148
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:05,120
The figure...the face...the body...the skin...

149
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,040
And the talent...it must be something like this, right?

150
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:10,680
Maybe not.

151
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,560
Stop talking and get to work!

152
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,920
Passengers who are flying to Korea, come this way, please.

153
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,760
We're ready now.

154
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:19,200
What are you waiting for?

155
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,160
Please come...get up!

156
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,120
Are you going to Korea?

157
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,600
This way, please.
Do you have a passport with you?

158
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:32,160
You're Mr. Glam!

159
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,920
Hello, Tid-Gift! Hello!

160
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:41,560
If I were really Mr. Glam,
why would I be sitting here working my ass off?

161
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:45,560
Wouldn’t it be better for me to sit in first class,
sipping wine and traveling around the world?

162
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,760
But where the hell is Mr. Glam right now?

163
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:52,040
Hey Chai, can’t you think?

164
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:55,080
Your brain isn’t just for keeping your ears apart, you know.

165
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,080
Use it for something useful.

166
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,280
Send a message in the group chat.

167
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:03,320
That's right. Good girl!

168
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:07,560
If it weren’t for you, I don’t know who else would come up with that.

169
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:14,440
Hello, Mr. Glam.

170
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:20,440
I’ve got something at the office I’d like to consult with you.

171
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,160
He replied, he replied!

172
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:30,160
HI PEECHAI NEE POM KAM LANG YUNG
(Hi, Chai, right now, I'm busy.)

173
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,440
Damn it, “kam,” not “kham.”

174
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:36,680
And why the hell would he type in karaoke?

175
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:41,960
Can you type in Thai?

176
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:45,200
Why would you even type like that to him?

177
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,800
Hey, he replied!

178
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,920
Sorry.

179
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:51,920
I’m preparing to return to Thailand to take care of some matters.

180
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:56,720
Coming back to handle some matters in Thailand...

181
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:59,080
Chai! That's it!

182
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:02,680
You have to do whatever it takes to lure Mr. Glam to meet us.

183
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,680
Then we’ll finally know who Mr. Glam really is.

184
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,920
See you soon.

185
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:32,680
Siri, why did you show me the mole?

186
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:33,680
Oh, wrong side.

187
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,400
Siri!

188
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:43,320
Oh, you don’t have to thank me, Madam, it’s just a small thing.

189
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:45,280
Yes, that's small.

190
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,560
Very small.

191
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:50,560
I told you to get a tattoo of the prison map,
so why did you get a QR code tattooed instead?

192
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,560
Hey, then why didn’t you get it tattooed yourself, Madam?

193
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,880
Because it hurts.

194
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,840
It hurt me too.

195
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,520
But it’s not that bad, Madam.

196
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,520
Here, try zooming in first.

197
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:06,160
What?

198
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,880
My hope of ever going outside...

199
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,720
is probably gone now, isn’t it?

200
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:12,160
My future...

201
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:15,640
Porn Airline’s future will probably end today.

202
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:18,200
Oh, Madam.

203
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:22,920
Don’t say that.
At least you’re not alone, Madam.

204
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:27,920
You still have me, stuck in prison for life, as your friend.

205
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:31,920
Thanks a lot, Siri, for stressing me out on a day I could smile.

206
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,880
So...is it good, Madam?

207
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:57,320
Sky...or maybe he’s not really Shark Yongke after all.

208
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,880
Then, let's prove it.

209
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:03,880
How can we prove that?

210
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,000
If he’s an idol, right?

211
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,800
then he has to be able to sing...

212
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,160
So make him sing for you.

213
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,560
But we’re on a plane!

214
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:15,640
He’s a person, not a caged bird that can sing anywhere.

215
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:16,640
You're an idiot!

216
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:22,000
Hey, that’s actually smart!

217
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,000
I always thought you were dumb, but this plan is sharp.

218
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:28,800
Alright, ladies and gentlemen,

219
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,720
coming up is a special entertainment

220
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:34,080
from Glamorous Airline.

221
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,600
The rule is simple...

222
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:37,440
if we hand the mic to someone,

223
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,440
that person has to sing.

224
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,800
Who should it be?

225
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:49,520
Who should it be?

226
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:59,440
No matter how far, even the distance to the moon…

227
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,200
Okay, that’s enough, not very good.

228
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:05,200
Let’s find someone with a really beautiful voice instead.

229
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:08,680
Who should it be?

230
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,040
Was that a ghost wailing from Wat Suthat?

231
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,400
Sounded like we just flew past that.

232
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,080
Let’s get someone else, someone who can really sing.

233
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,960
Like an idol or something.

234
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:32,520
Good idea, right?

235
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:33,080
Yeah, good.

236
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:37,080
So, who’s it gonna be?
Who’ll it accidentally turn out to be?

237
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,000
Chaba.

238
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:42,880
Huh?

239
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,080
I’ve sung so much my throat’s swollen already.

240
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,240
Let somebody else do it.

241
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:50,240
Fine, then it really has to be someone else.

242
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:57,760
Go ahead, sing!
Our passengers are waiting.

243
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:06,560
There must be something wrong somewhere...

244
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:09,200
Never once have I understood...

245
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,680
What he did, I did it too...

246
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:15,920
But I could never pull it off even once...

247
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,160
Uh, wait, wait...

248
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:22,160
Do you need to take a dump?

249
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,840
You can go first if you'd like.

250
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:28,400
See? I told you.

251
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,440
There’s no way he’s Shark Yongke.

252
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,440
That voice was like a dog getting its tail stepped on.

253
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,920
Excuse me, please lower your voice.

254
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,920
Let’s not disturb the others.

255
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,320
And he's eager to sing, huh?

256
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:48,800
Tid-Gift, think about it.

257
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:52,760
How are you going to use your bullshit skills to lure Mr. Glam out?

258
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:55,760
Hey, are you giving praise or insulting? Pick one.

259
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:01,080
But if I had to pick the skill I’m best at,

260
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:05,080
it’d be acting. I learned it from Piangduan.

261
